translated:
Jernström, Åke Jakob, Chief Surveyor, Vänersborg, b. 26/7/98 in Lidköping, the son of the dentist Isac J. and August Fröberg. Married to Gerda Isaksson in 1928. Children: Uil-la-Brita (born in 1931), Gunnar (born in 1938). 

Education: Graduated from Skara High School in 1916. Studies at KTH (V) from 1916 to 1920. Surveyor examination in 1922. Cultural engineering examination in 1926. 

Career: Assistant Surveyor in Skaraborg County from 1922 to 1928. Assistant in Västerbotten County from 1928 to 1930. Temporary District Surveyor in Väddö District in 1930. Permanent Surveyor in Örebro County from 1931 to 1933. Temporary District Surveyor in Ronneby District from 1933 to 1935. Appointed as a bureau engineer in the Surveyor Authority in 1933. Served in the authority from 1935 to 1936. Appointed as District Surveyor in Lindes District in 1935. Chief Surveyor in Älvsborg County since 1936. Chairman of the expropriation board in 1941 and the board of Älvsborg City Mortgage Association and Västergötland-Dals Housing Credit Association in 1942. Member of the crisis management board for Älvsborg County northern area in 1944 and the board of System A-B in Vänersborg in 1945. 

Recipient of the Royal Order of the North Star (RNO.)
